This paper deals with the theory of lambda-calculus and its equivalences, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). It also involves the study of extensionality and the omega-rule, which are topics related to programming languages (cs.PL) and type theory (cs.TL). The paper also discusses the characterization of Böhm trees, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and formal languages (cs.FL).
